m_skipEntries

java.lang.String m_skipEntries
Date time stamps that should be skipped - i.e. not considered as an increment. E.g financial markets don't trade on the weekend, so the difference between friday closing and the following monday closing is one time unit (and not three). Can accept strings such as "sat", "sunday", "jan", "august", or explicit dates (with optional formatting string) such as "2011-07-04@yyyy-MM-dd", or integers. Integers are interpreted with respect to the periodicity - e.g for daily data they are interpreted as day of the year; for hourly data, hour of the day; weekly data, week of the year.
